In data analysis, recent technical approaches have included adjustment of the software reading platforms for simultaneous detection of genotypes and mutants of clinical importance (
 Germer 
  et al., 2013
 ), and partial sequencing of the HBV S gene with high sensitivity (98.64%), considering that portion as the site of most drug-resistance mutations (
 Wang 
  et al., 2013
 ). Nevertheless, implementation of NGS in clinical settings is increasing, particularly for detecting low-abundance drug-resistance patterns such as in HIV and HCV (
 Palmer 
  et al., 2005
 ; 
 Verbinnen 
  et al., 2010
 ). Nucleotide sequencing of HCV sub-genomic regions is now the method of choice for genotyping.
